---PART---

PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly budget limit.

STRUCTURE: Dashboard Screen
MARKER: dashboard_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing all budget categories and their balances
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a section for each budget category with its name, current balance, and budget limit, and a summary at the bottom with total balance and percentage spent.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the "Add Category" button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and budget limit. The new category is added to the list and displayed on the dashboard.

WHEN: Update Category Balance
MARKER: update_category_balance
INTENT: user updates the balance of a budget category
TAGS: #card, #form, #user
---
When the user taps the "Edit" button on a category card, a form appears. The user updates the balance and saves the changes. The updated balance is reflected in the category card and the summary at the bottom.

ASSERT: Category Balance Validation
MARKER: category_balance_validation
INTENT: ensure category balance does not exceed budget limit
TAGS: #error, #message, #user, #validation
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its budget limit. If the user tries to add more than the budget limit, an error message appears.

SURFACE: Error Messages
MARKER: error_messages
INTENT: error messages displayed to the user
TAGS: #error, #message, #user
---
The error message reads "Balance cannot exceed budget limit" when the user tries to add more than the budget limit.

STRUCTURE: Stats Panel
MARKER: stats_panel
INTENT: displays summary statistics for budget categories
TAGS: #panel, #table, #task
---
The screen has a section below the task section with a header "Budget Summary". This section includes a pie chart showing the distribution of balances across all categories and a table listing each category with its name, current balance, and budget limit. Below the table, there is a summary row showing the total balance and the percentage of the total budget spent.
---PART---

PART: Tasks
NAME: Tasks
STATUS: draft

STRUCTURE: Task Screen
MARKER: task_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing all tasks
LOCK: approved
TAGS: #list, #task
---
The screen has a top bar with the app name, a scrollable list of task cards, and a floating add button in the bottom right. Additionally, there is a "Yay" button at the bottom right.

WHEN: Complete Task
MARKER: complete_task
INTENT: user marks a task as done
TAGS: #card, #list, #task, #user
---
When the user taps the checkbox on a task card, the task status changes to complete. The card moves to the bottom of the list with a strikethrough style.

WHEN: Tap Task Completed Button
MARKER: tap_task_completed_button
INTENT: user confirms task completion
TAGS: #card, #dialog, #list, #task, #user
---
When the user taps the "Task Completed" button on a task card, a confirmation dialog appears. If the user confirms, the task is marked as complete and moved to the bottom of the list with a strikethrough style. If the user cancels, the task remains unchanged.

WHEN: Tap Yay Button
MARKER: tap_yay_button
INTENT: user taps the "Yay" button to create a new task
TAGS: #form, #list, #task, #user
---
When the user taps the "Yay" button, a new task form appears. The user fills in the title and confirms. The new task appears at the top of the list.